      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, knead, and bulk ferment, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{salt-table}}, and {{caster-sugar}}. Add the {{water}} gradually, the dough should be stiff, not sticky. Knead for 10 minutes until very smooth and firm; it should feel noticeably stiffer than a standard bread dough. Cover and bulk ferment for 1 hour until risen but not necessarily doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide into 8 pieces (about 100 g each). Shape each into a smooth ball, then poke a finger through the centre and stretch the ring to about 10 cm across. The hole should be generous. It will close up during the boil and bake. Place on a floured tray, cover, and prove for 30 minutes. Heat the oven to 220°C (200°C fan). Line two baking trays with oiled baking paper (not dry parchment, which sticks).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Boil and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring a large, wide pan of {{water}} to a rolling boil. Add the {{golden-syrup}} and {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} if using. Drop the bagels in 2 or 3 at a time. They will sink then float. Boil for 45 seconds per side. Lift out with a slotted spoon, drain briefly, and place on the oiled trays. Top with seeds or toppings of your choice, pressing them in gently. Bake for 20 to 22 minutes until deep golden with a shiny surface. Cool on a wire rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
